& =\int_{0}^{1} \sqrt{1+4 x^{2}} d x=\frac{1}{2} \int_{0}^{2} \sqrt{1+u^{2}} d u \\
& =\left.\frac{1}{2}\left\{\frac{1}{2} u \sqrt{1+u^{2}}+\frac{1}{2} \ln \left(u+\sqrt{1+u^{2}}\right)\right\}\right|_{0} ^{2}=\frac{1}{2} \sqrt{5}+\frac{1}{4} \ln (2+\sqrt{5})
