EXAMPLE 1. $\int_{1}^{5} \frac{d x}{\sqrt{x^{4}-1}}$ converges, since $\lim _{x \rightarrow 1+}(x-1)^{1 / 2} \cdot \frac{1}{\left(x^{4}-1\right)^{1 / 2}}=\lim _{x \rightarrow 1+} \sqrt{\frac{x-1}{x^{4}-1}}=\frac{1}{2}$.

