Letting $v=(1-u) t$, we have

$$
\begin{aligned}
\int_{v=0}^{1-u} v^{(\beta / 2)-1}(1-u-v)^{\gamma / 2} d v & =(1-u)^{(\beta+\gamma) / 2} \int_{t=0}^{1} t^{(\beta / 2)-1}(1-t)^{\gamma / 2} d t \\
& =(1-u)^{(\beta+\gamma) / 2} \frac{\Gamma(\beta / 2) \Gamma(\gamma / 2+1)}{\Gamma[(\beta+\gamma) / 2+1]}
