15.24. Prove the duplication formula $2^{2 p-1} \Gamma(\mathrm{p}) \Gamma\left(p+\frac{1}{2}\right)=\sqrt{\pi} \Gamma(2 p)$.

Let $I=\int_{0}^{\pi / 2} \sin ^{2 p} x d x, J=\int_{0}^{\pi / 2} \sin ^{2 p} 2 x d x$.

